    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine Domini. Anno quintodecimo principatus domni <persName
                            ref="#people/327" key="#Princeps">Gisolfi</persName>
                        <rs key="#Princeps">princips</rs>, mense maius, quinta indictione. Quadam
                        vero die, dum superius domnus princeps secundum glorie dingnitatis sue
                        residente sacratissimo Salernitano palatio, et ante eius vestigiis
                        astantibus <persName key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus" ref="#people/4173"
                            >Lando</persName>
                        <rs key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus">gastaldeus</rs> et <persName key="#Judge"
                            ref="#people/4174">Moncola</persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudex</rs> et aliis novilibus, tunc in eadem presentia
                        venerunt idest <name ref="Petrus">Petrus</name> natibus Francorum fines, seu
                        nec non et ibidem venit <persName ref="#people/4175" key="#Priests #Abbots"
                            >Adelchisi</persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs> et <rs key="#Abbots">abbatis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Churches">ecclesie</rs><orgName ref="#juridical_persons/77"
                            key="#Churches #Private_foundations"> Sancti Maximi</orgName>, quem
                        domnus Guaiferius princeps a novo fundamine construxit intus hanc <placeName
                            ref="#places/84" key="#Cities">Salernitanam</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Cities">cibitatem</rs>, unaque cum <persName ref="#people/4176"
                            key="#Notary #Advocatus">Alderissi</persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarium</rs>
                        <rs key="#Advocatus">advocatorem</rs> suum, et continuo ipse quidem
                        Adelchisi presbiter et abbas, una cum ipso advocatorem suum causare ceperunt
                        adversus ipsum Petrus dicentes: "hic iste Petrus, qui vestris adest
                        presentiis, tenet rebus in locum <placeName ref="#places/4014"
                            key="#Villages/settlements #Fiscal_property #Object #Function #Redistributive #Inflow #Inheritance #Confiscation #Outflow #Allocation_to_individuals #Property_of_persons_without_heirs #Property_of_criminals/political_traitors"
                            >Nucerie</placeName>, qui fui <name
                            ref="Iohannelgari monachus f. Iohanni">Iohannelgari</name> monacho
                        filius Iohanni, que in eadem sanctam ecclesiam offertum fui per ipsum
                        Iohannelgari et per ipsa uxor eius et per <name
                            ref="Iohannes clericus f. Iohannelgari">Iohannes</name> clericus filius
                        eius". Cum quo ipse Petrus unaque cum <persName
                            key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus #Advocatus" ref="#people/4177"
                            >Guaiferium</persName>
                        <rs key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus">gastaldeum</rs>
                        <rs key="#Advocatus">advocatorem</rs> suum taliter adversus se causantes
                        audierunt, responsum retdiderunt dicentes: "Verum est, ut rebus ipsa
                        tenere", pro qua dicebant a Palatio ei concessa fuisse; et statim in eadem
                        presentia ipse quidem Petrus ostendit ibidem unum preceptum (…) </ab>
                    <ab>(...) et dum relectus est ipse preceptum, continebant qualiter domnus
                            <persName key="#Princeps" ref="#people/298">Guaimarius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Princeps">princeps</rs>, <rs key="#Intercessory">per rogum</rs>
                        <persName ref="#people/4145" key="#Count">Guidoni</persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comitis</rs> et <rs key="#Other_palatine_officer"
                            >theusaurarii</rs> fratri suo, concesserad eidem Petri <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Function #Redistributive #Inflow #Inheritance #Confiscation #Outflow #Allocation_to_individuals #Property_of_persons_without_heirs #Property_of_criminals/political_traitors"
                            >omnis rebus ipsius Iohannelgari</rs> de predicto locum Nucerie (…)</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
